.SH "NAME"
tblite-param \- Export, import and manipulate tight\-binding parameter files
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBtblite param\fP [\fIoptions\fP] \fIinput\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
Allows to export parameter files from the internal storage or merge parameter files with an internal base parametrization.
The \fIinput\fP variable must be present or an internal parametrization should be selected.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-\-output\fP \fIstring\fP
.RS 4
Output file to write parameters
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-method\fP \fIstring\fP
.RS 4
Name of the parametrisation to use, supported are
\fIgfn1\fP, \fIipea1\fP and \fIgfn2\fP
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-version\fP
.RS 4
Prints version number and citation
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Show this message
.RE
.sp
Command line arguments can be read from an indirect file / response file by specifying the file with @\fIname\fP in the command line.
Each line in the file is interpreted as command line argument, shell like escape sequences are not available.
The file can contain further @\fIname\fP inputs. If the file cannot be the argument is used literally.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.sp
\fBtblite\fP(1)
